title._content: HMAS SYDNEY with Indigenous people on outriggers in foreground

description._content:
This photograph is part of a collection of items relating to the naval career of John Berhcmans Kiley. Kiley served on HMAS SYDNEY from 1926 to 1927 and in 1927 the vessel visited New Caledonia and the Solomon Islands where this image was probably captured.

The Australian National Maritime Museum undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. If you can identify a person, vessel or landmark, write the details in the Comments box below. 

Thank you for helping caption this important historical image.

Object number ANMS0823[253]

John Berchmans Kiley Collection
